# English Journal — agent onboarding

**Before reading or editing source files, read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) at the repo root.**

It covers architecture, data model, API routes, auth, AI layer, file map, conventions, and where to change things.

## Quick facts

- Next.js 15 App Router + Supabase (auth + Postgres) + Vercel AI SDK (Gemini/OpenAI)
- Main UI: `AuthGate` → `JournalApp` (paragraph editor + drawers + `TopActionsMenu` hamburger on mobile)
- Persistence: `journal_entries` + `journal_paragraphs` via `src/lib/entries-db.ts`; `user_preferences` via `src/lib/preferences-db.ts`
- Use `StoredJournalEntry` / `JournalParagraph` / `AnalysisPreferences` types
- Analysis is per-paragraph with optional focus areas; `/api/analyze` is public; entry and preferences APIs require auth
